On Wed, 2005-05-11 at 12:35 +1000, Dennis Hotson wrote:&lt;BR&gt;
&gt; I&#39;ve been looking at heritrix for about a week now and it&#39;s working&lt;BR&gt;
&gt; really well. I&#39;ve got it crawling and inserting pages into a database.&lt;BR&gt;
&gt; &lt;BR&gt;
&gt; I&#39;m just wondering what kind of scheduling functionality is available in&lt;BR&gt;
&gt; heritrix.&lt;BR&gt;
&gt; For example.. is there a way to schedule a job to run at 2:00 AM every 3&lt;BR&gt;
&gt; days? &lt;BR&gt;
&lt;BR&gt;
&lt;BR&gt;
Ok.. I&#39;ve been doing some more investigation and I&#39;m thinking of using&lt;BR&gt;
another java scheduler (&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.opensymphony.com/quartz/)&quot;&gt;http://www.opensymphony.com/quartz/)&lt;/a&gt; and I was&lt;BR&gt;
thinking of setting up jobs in heritrix via the JMX interface.&lt;BR&gt;
The only problem is that the JMX interface appears to be quite primitive&lt;BR&gt;
in comparison to the web interface. :P&lt;BR&gt;
Are there plans to improve the functionality of the JMX interface? If&lt;BR&gt;
not.. How hard would it be to do it myself?&lt;BR&gt;
&lt;BR&gt;
Otherwise.. are there any other ways I can automate configuring/running&lt;BR&gt;
jobs in heritrix?&lt;BR&gt;
The web interface is very nice, but I need to be able to automate the&lt;BR&gt;
process so that a real user isn&#39;t required.&lt;BR&gt;
&lt;BR&gt;
Any ideas? :)&lt;BR&gt;
&lt;BR&gt;
&lt;BR&gt;
Regards,&lt;BR&gt;
Dennis&lt;BR&gt;
&lt;BR&gt;
&lt;BR&gt;
